<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1162> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1162" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap.: idem qui pr. erat; see Degrassi 42f., 434f., and especially 116." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1161> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1161" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the accumulation of offices involved, see Mommsen, Str. 1.514, note 1, and Degrassi 116. This Praetor is omitted by Stella Maranca, 294f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1160> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1160" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Postumius died in office, and Iunius abdicated (Fast. Cap., Degrassi, 42f., 116, 434f.). See Lübker no. 22 on Postumius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1125> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1125" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Naevius fr. 19, see Fränkel, Hermes 70 (1935) 59ff.; and the articles cited in 263, note 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1124> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1124" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Polyb. 1.17.6; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd. (Albino et Vituitulo); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Zon. 8.10; Degrassi, 40f., 115, 432f. Both Consuls besieged and finally captured the town of Agrigentum (Polyb. 1.17.6-20.2; Diod. 23.7-9; Zon. 8.10; cf. Naev. fr. 19;\n     Frontin. Str. 2.1.4)." .
